        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Way back when I was going to camp my COS, I had a necro friend that I was trying to convince to come with me to get herself a copy. It actually broke out into an small argument as she thought the thing was not worth the effort to get. "I have Gather Shadows as a spell, why the hell would I need an item that did the same?"</P><P>To those that are making feeble arguments as to why a pre-nerf COS is not worth it, I shake my head. If you were to take a poll of every necro in the game, and tell them if they could chose any 3 items in the game to keep, and could never get another item, I bet 98.5% of the necros out there would have their pre-nerf COS's on that list. </P><P>That is a powerful statement, and well deserved. A pre-nerf COS becomes a strategic tool that greatly increases the scope of what you can do. If you have not figured out the worth of this item by now, you are just not thinking hard enough. Period.</P><P><BR>Cheers,<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=63522">Ancagalon the Black </a><BR>Warlock - Terris Thule<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
